DD_Attribute_Full.name: data_set_name
DD_Attribute_Full.definition: The data_set_name element provides the full name given to a data set or a data product. The data_set_name typically identifies the instrument that acquired the data, the target of that instrument, and the processing level of the data. Example value: MR9/VO1/VO2 MARS IMAGING SCIENCE SUBSYSTEM/VIS 5 CLOUD V1.0. See also: data_set_id. Note: In PDS, the data_set_name is constructed according to standards outlined in the Standards Reference. Note: This element is defined in the AMMOS Magellan catalog as an alias for file_name to provide backward compatibility
